Gazpacho also known as Gaspacho, is a cold soup and drink made of raw, blended vegetables. The Spanish dish is mainly made of chopped tomatoes, cucumbers, onions, garlic, oil, and vinegar, and is best served cold with bread, tacos, or hard-boiled eggs The ingredients, texture, and thickness of gazpacho vary regionally and between different cooks. Some may include fruits like watermelon, and apples, while others prefer vegetables. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Using a blender, blend 1 tomato, 1/2 of the cucumber, 1/2 of the onion, 1/4 of the bell pepper, and 1/2 cup of the tomato juice until smooth. Step 2 Transfer the mixture to a bowl and add the remaining tomato juice, oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, and hot sauce. Step 3 Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours. Step 4 Dice the remaining vegetables and refrigerate them separately from the soup. Step 5 Stir the garlic and chopped vegetables into the soup before serving with a topping of vegetables. Then serve cold. Enjoy with garlic bread or hard-boiled eggs.